 {"id":"bd-reb0e","title":"[fuzz-harness] fuzz_pidfd_timer: TimerDelete leaves id so kernel could reuse it (same class as bd-2t616 / bd-tw26d)","description":"Same id-reuse pattern as bd-2t616 (PidfdClose) and bd-tw26d (fuzz_socket MarkStale). TimerDelete sets table.timers[idx] = (id, Stale) after successfully deleting the timer. The kernel allocates timer ids from a shared space — subsequent TimerCreate may return the same numeric id. Then ops on the stale slot's id hit the new live timer and the 'must fail on stale id' assertion trips. Fix: store (-1, Stale) for poison.","notes":"Fixed in subsequent commit — TimerDelete now stores (-1, Stale). 60s re-fuzz clean.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T16:57:56.393308932Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-23T17:01:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T17:01:00Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-rftd","title":"process: execute spawn_exec_ops.json fixture family through harness matrix","description":"Concrete gap: crates/frankenlibc-harness/tests/spawn_exec_ops_conformance_test.rs validates schema and coverage for tests/conformance/fixtures/spawn_exec_ops.json but never drives those cases through the harness subprocess. Add isolated matrix execution for posix_spawn/execve/system fixtures, assert expected_output and host parity in strict/hardened modes, and fix any process-wrapper mismatches the new coverage exposes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T05:56:34.380556045Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T15:57:46.979346551Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T15:57:46.977092185Z","close_reason":"Executed spawn_exec_ops fixture coverage through the isolated harness conformance matrix path and verified with rch.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-rgzu","title":"syscall: fspick NULL pathname with nonzero flags should preserve unprivileged EPERM host contract","description":"Host glibc returns EPERM for fspick(AT_FDCWD, NULL, 1) on this unprivileged host. Add ABI regression coverage so nonzero flags preserve the observed privilege-first result.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:13:32.348267860Z","created_by":"AmberSignal","updated_at":"2026-04-21T21:48:12.608365662Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T21:48:12.606091515Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"bd-ris3r","title":"FUZZ: keyring (add_key/request_key/keyctl) structure-aware harness","description":"crates/frankenlibc-fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_keyring.rs. Linux kernel keyring family — add_key/request_key/keyctl — has rich attacker-controlled string + payload surface and historical CVEs. Harness drives all three across known-failing keyring ids + bogus payloads. add_key(type, desc, payload, plen, keyring_id), request_key(type, desc, callout_info, dest_keyring), keyctl(cmd, args*4) with 30+ KEYCTL_* commands. Invariants: rc is -1 or non-negative key serial / count; never panic; bounded plen + bounded callout/desc strings to avoid stalling.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T10:20:38.593698240Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T10:20:38.593698240Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-ris3r","title":"FUZZ: keyring (add_key/request_key/keyctl) structure-aware harness","description":"crates/frankenlibc-fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_keyring.rs. Linux kernel keyring family — add_key/request_key/keyctl — has rich attacker-controlled string + payload surface and historical CVEs. Harness drives all three across known-failing keyring ids + bogus payloads. add_key(type, desc, payload, plen, keyring_id), request_key(type, desc, callout_info, dest_keyring), keyctl(cmd, args*4) with 30+ KEYCTL_* commands. Invariants: rc is -1 or non-negative key serial / count; never panic; bounded plen + bounded callout/desc strings to avoid stalling.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T10:20:38.593698240Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T10:27:27.596020060Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T10:27:27.594015566Z","close_reason":"Shipped: fuzz_keyring.rs covers add_key/request_key/keyctl over allowlisted key types + 33 KEYCTL_* commands. 32-byte guarded payload buffer. Self-caught OOM on keyctl size-arg interpretation, bounded all 4 args modulo 16KB before ship. 5.3M runs at 87K exec/s clean. Landed in ba66daee.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-rjsa","title":"syscall: process_mrelease pidfd=0 should mirror invalid-pidfd errno matrix","description":"Host glibc reports the same invalid-descriptor matrix for process_mrelease with pidfd=0 as with pidfd=-1: EBADF for flags=0 and EINVAL for flags!=0. Add focused ABI regression coverage so the wrapper stays exact on both invalid-pidfd shapes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:20:45.425524704Z","created_by":"AmberSignal","updated_at":"2026-04-21T19:28:08.878281930Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T19:28:08.875988118Z","close_reason":"Pinned process_mrelease pidfd=0 behavior to exact host EBADF/EINVAL parity for flags zero and nonzero","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
